---
/* ParcelMap
 *
 * Schematic, not GIS-precise. Shows the four roads bounding the K-Nova /
 * Jahn Farm parcel and the Foxfire neighborhood to the south. The diagram
 * is intentionally simple, set in the brand palette, and labeled in the
 * brand's three faces (serif for placenames, mono for road designations
 * and numbers, sans for body lines). A small Ohio context inset orients
 * out-of-area readers.
 */
---

<figure class="map-figure">
  <svg
    class="map-svg"
    viewBox="0 0 640 520"
    xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
    role="img"
    aria-labelledby="map-title map-desc"
    preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet"
  >
    <title id="map-title">Map of the K-Nova / Jahn Farm parcel</title>
    <desc id="map-desc">
      Schematic showing approximately 266.971 acres rezoned to a Planned Industrial
      District, bounded by Durrett Road on the north, State Route 104 on the east,
      State Route 762 on the south, and Borror Road on the west. The Foxfire
      neighborhood is south of State Route 762. Inset shows the location in Ohio.
    </desc>

    <!-- Background -->
    <rect x="0" y="0" width="640" height="520" style="fill: var(--paper-2);" />

    <!-- Parcel -->
    <rect
      x="120" y="100" width="400" height="280"
      style="fill: var(--bone); stroke: var(--ink); stroke-width: 1.5;"
    />

    <!-- Road lines -->
    <line x1="80" y1="100" x2="560" y2="100" style="stroke: var(--ink); stroke-width: 2;" />
    <line x1="80" y1="380" x2="560" y2="380" style="stroke: var(--ink); stroke-width: 2;" />
    <line x1="120" y1="60" x2="120" y2="420" style="stroke: var(--ink); stroke-width: 2;" />
    <line x1="520" y1="60" x2="520" y2="420" style="stroke: var(--ink); stroke-width: 2;" />

    <!-- Road labels -->
    <text x="320" y="86"
      text-anchor="middle"
      style="font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: 0.08em; fill: var(--ink);">
      DURRETT ROAD
    </text>
    <text x="320" y="406"
      text-anchor="middle"
      style="font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: 0.08em; fill: var(--ink);">
      STATE ROUTE 762
    </text>
    <text
      transform="rotate(-90 100 240)"
      x="100" y="240"
      text-anchor="middle"
      style="font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: 0.08em; fill: var(--ink);">
      BORROR ROAD
    </text>
    <text
      transform="rotate(90 540 240)"
      x="540" y="240"
      text-anchor="middle"
      style="font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: 0.08em; fill: var(--ink);">
      STATE ROUTE 104
    </text>

    <!-- Parcel label group -->
    <text x="320" y="218"
      text-anchor="middle"
      style="font-family: var(--headline); font-size: 22px; fill: var(--ink); font-weight: 500;">
      K-Nova / Jahn Farm
    </text>
    <text x="320" y="252"
      text-anchor="middle"
      style="font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 26px; fill: var(--ink); font-feature-settings: 'tnum'; letter-spacing: -0.005em;">
      266.971 ac
    </text>
    <text x="320" y="280"
      text-anchor="middle"
      style="font-family: var(--body); font-size: 13px; fill: var(--text-soft);">
      Planned Industrial District (Ord 2024-07)
    </text>

    <!-- Foxfire band -->
    <rect
      x="180" y="425" width="280" height="55"
      style="fill: var(--moss); stroke: var(--moss-2); stroke-width: 1; stroke-dasharray: 4 3;"
    />
    <text x="320" y="460"
      text-anchor="middle"
      style="font-family: var(--headline); font-size: 16px; fill: var(--ink); font-weight: 500;">
      Foxfire neighborhood
    </text>

    <!-- Ohio context inset (top-left) -->
    <g transform="translate(28 32)">
      <rect x="-4" y="-12" width="100" height="80"
        style="fill: var(--paper); stroke: var(--rule-soft); stroke-width: 1;" />
      <text x="46" y="0"
        text-anchor="middle"
        style="font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 0.08em; fill: var(--text-mute);">
        OHIO
      </text>
      <!-- Stylized Ohio outline (schematic, not GIS) -->
      <path
        d="M 4 14 L 22 11 L 36 6 L 50 4 L 60 6 L 74 9 L 86 12 L 88 24 L 84 32 L 86 40 L 82 48 L 72 54 L 60 58 L 46 60 L 30 56 L 18 50 L 8 42 L 2 32 L 4 22 Z"
        style="fill: var(--bone); stroke: var(--ink); stroke-width: 1; stroke-linejoin: round;"
      />
      <!-- Pickaway County dot -->
      <circle cx="46" cy="40" r="3" style="fill: var(--ink);" />
      <line x1="46" y1="40" x2="46" y2="56" style="stroke: var(--ink); stroke-width: 0.6;" />
      <text x="46" y="68"
        text-anchor="middle"
        style="font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 8px; letter-spacing: 0.06em; fill: var(--ink);">
        PICKAWAY CO.
      </text>
    </g>

    <!-- Compass -->
    <g transform="translate(595 50)">
      <circle r="20" style="fill: none; stroke: var(--rule-soft); stroke-width: 1;" />
      <path d="M 0 -12 L 5 4 L 0 0 L -5 4 Z" style="fill: var(--ink);" />
      <text y="-26" text-anchor="middle"
        style="font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10px; fill: var(--text-mute); letter-spacing: 0.06em;">
        N
      </text>
    </g>

    <!-- Scale bar (≈ 0.5 mile reference) -->
    <g transform="translate(40 490)">
      <line x1="0" y1="0" x2="80" y2="0" style="stroke: var(--ink); stroke-width: 1.5;" />
      <line x1="0" y1="-3" x2="0" y2="3" style="stroke: var(--ink); stroke-width: 1.5;" />
      <line x1="80" y1="-3" x2="80" y2="3" style="stroke: var(--ink); stroke-width: 1.5;" />
      <text x="40" y="-8" text-anchor="middle"
        style="font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10px; fill: var(--text-soft); letter-spacing: 0.04em;">
        APPROX 0.5 MI
      </text>
    </g>
  </svg>

  <div class="map-legend">
    <h3>What you are looking at.</h3>
    <dl>
      <dt class="mono">Parcel</dt>
      <dd>Approximately 266.971 acres rezoned to Planned Industrial District for data centers.</dd>
      <dt class="mono">Borders</dt>
      <dd>SR 104 east, Durrett Road north, Borror Road west, SR 762 south.</dd>
      <dt class="mono">Foxfire</dt>
      <dd>Residential neighborhood directly south of the parcel, separated by SR 762.</dd>
      <dt class="mono">Scale</dt>
      <dd>The parcel is roughly half a mile across, the size of about 200 football fields.</dd>
    </dl>
    <p class="map-caption">
      Schematic only. Boundaries follow the legal description in Ordinance 2024-07. For an
      official parcel map, see the Pickaway County Auditor.
    </p>
  </div>
</figure>
